HEADWORD: Cacomixl
<hw>Ca"co*mix`l</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Mexican name.]</ety> <def>A North American carnivore
(<spn>Bassaris astuta</spn>), about the size of a cat, related to the
raccoons. It inhabits Mexico, Texas, and California.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cacoon</ent>⟦br⟧
